laboratory_examinations.procedure_name: CT ABD & PELVIS W & W/O CONTRAST, ADDL SECTIONS
laboratory_examinations.findings: Unremarkable liver with multiple hemangiomas measuring up to 6 cm; normal pancreas with no lesions; normal spleen; normal adrenal glands; unremarkable kidneys with no hydronephrosis; distended bladder; no intestinal obstruction; distended appendix with associated soft tissue strain and appendicolith; no abscess formation; no free fluid in pelvis; mildly enlarged prostate; few prominent right lower quadrant lymph nodes likely reactive; no abdominal aortic aneurysm; no atherosclerotic disease; no evidence of osseous lesions or acute fracture.
